class Solution {
public:
    int smallestRepunitDivByK(int k) {
        int res = 0, n = 1;
        while (true) {
            if (n % k == 0) return ++res;
            n = n * 10 + 1;
        }
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(k))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: We use a simple iterative approach to generate the smallest positive integer n that is divisible by k and only contains the digit 1. We start with n = 1 and keep appending 1 to the end of n until we find a number that is divisible by k. The time complexity is O(log(k)) because we are essentially generating a number of length log(k) in the worst case.

